Over-representation Analysis in R

# set global chunk options
library(knitr)
opts_chunk$set(size='tiny')

Purpose

The whole purpose of this vignette/cheatsheet is to show different approaches for testing for significance of certain over-representation in one group of genes vs another.

The data

we’ll take a look what is enriched in the sixth cluster compare to the rest

KEGG annotation

GOstats package

p <- new("KEGGHyperGParams",
         geneIds = gcSample[[6]],
         universeGeneIds = unique(unlist(gcSample)),
         annotation = "org.Hs.eg.db",
         pvalueCutoff = 1,
         testDirection = "over")
xke1 <- hyperGTest(p)
res <- summary(xke1)[, c("KEGGID", "Term", "Pvalue", "Count", "Size")]
kable(head(res))

GO Biological Process (BP) annotation

PFAM

GOstats package

p <- new("PFAMHyperGParams",
         geneIds = gcSample[[6]],
         universeGeneIds = unique(unlist(gcSample)),
         annotation = "org.Hs.eg.db",
         pvalueCutoff = 1,
         testDirection = "over")
xpfam <- hyperGTest(p)
## 'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns
## 'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns
## 'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns
res <- head(summary(xpfam)) # Top 6

# Use rvest package to obtain descriptions for the PFAM terms
pfam_descr <- lapply(res$Term, 
                     function(term_i) {
                       read_html(paste0("https://pfam.xfam.org/family/", 
                                        term_i)) %>%
                         html_nodes("h1") %>% 
                         html_text() %>%
                         .[grepl("Summary: ", .)]
                     }) %>% 
  unlist() %>% 
  gsub("Summary: (.*)", "\\1", .)

res <- cbind(res, Description = pfam_descr)
kable(res)

Custom stuff

Taking advantage of enricher function from clusterProfiler

# randomly assign genes to 20 clusters
set.seed(1236)
setnum <- replicate(length(unique(unlist(gcSample))), sample(1:20, 1))
setnum <- paste("set", setnum, sep = '')
TERM2GENE <- data.frame(term = setnum, gene = unique(unlist(gcSample)),
                        stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
TERM2NAME <- data.frame(term = setnum, 
                        name = paste("Description: ", setnum, sep = ''),
                        stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
xfake <- enricher(gene = gcSample[[6]], 
                  pvalueCutoff = 1,
                  universe = unique(unlist(gcSample)),
                  minGSSize = 0,
                  qvalueCutoff = 1,
                  TERM2GENE = TERM2GENE, 
                  TERM2NAME = TERM2NAME)
res <- xfake@result[, c("ID", "Description", "pvalue", "GeneRatio", "BgRatio")]
rownames(res) <- NULL
kable(head(res))
ID Description pvalue GeneRatio BgRatio
set4 Description: set4 0.0325057 38/585 189/3890
set3 Description: set3 0.1351999 37/585 206/3890
set9 Description: set9 0.1851092 34/585 194/3890
set17 Description: set17 0.1957386 33/585 189/3890
set15 Description: set15 0.2530519 33/585 195/3890
set10 Description: set10 0.3478749 29/585 178/3890 
cnetplot(xfake, layout = "fr", cex_label_category = 0.8, cex_label_gene = 0.4)
